						 <p>This is stupid in all the right ways. +1</p> <p>Actually, I am not going to <em>retract</em> my previous statement, but I am going to blatantly contradict it; <em>this is genius</em>. I realize, now, that this is you melted and put in a syringe and injected straight into the SCP wiki. If I were to get the question &quot;Hey, who is that handsome ex-military man <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cadavercommander" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3187823&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1521516212" alt="CadaverCommander" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3187823)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cadavercommander" >CadaverCommander</a></span>?&quot; I would reply by linking this article, and they would go &quot;Oh my, I understand now.&quot; and they would go about their day understanding exactly who Mr. Commander is. This feels very very <em>you</em>. The only thing it is missing is some naval combat.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
